  <span id="freeText13207504148636470312" style="display:none">This is a Modern Scholar CD series I picked up at the library and became engrossed in from the first sentence. Sometimes it is hard to find books tape that I can really focus on, but now I'm looking into more CD sets in the Modern Scholar series. It's basically a lecture series given by a university professor on various topics, this one being on Ben Franklin. I've always been fascinated with Benjamin Franklin and now I know much more about him! His accomplishments and genious as well as his warts and failings, and the ways he didn't always live up to his own high standards. Yet he is one of the most beloved figures in American History. </span>
